    "title": "China says appreciates U.S. position on ZTE",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "BEIJING (Reuters) - China’s Foreign Ministry said on Monday the country appreciated the U.S. position on ZTE Corp, following a pledge by President Donald Trump to help the firm “get back into business, fast.”\nForeign Ministry spokesman Lu Kang said China is in close communications with the United States on ZTE, which suspended its main operations after the U.S. Commerce Department banned American firms from selling to ZTE for seven years.\nReporting by Sue-Lin Wong; Writing by Beijing Monitoring Desk; Editing by Darren Schuettler\n ",
